.TH PROCVW 1 "April 2026" "procvw 1.0" "FreeBSD General Commands Manual"

.SH NAME
procvw \- A FreeBSD process viewer with tree, JSON, snapshot, and color support

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B procvw
[\-u USER] [\-f FILTER] [\-p PID]
[\-s {cpu,mem,pid,rss,cmd}] [\-b]
[\-n NUMBER] [\-\-color]
[\-\-tree] [\-\-table]
[\-\-cpu-all] [\-\-cpu-threshold VALUE]
[\-\-tree-depth N]
[\-\-json] [\-\-json-view]
[\-\-load FILE] [\-\-save FILE]

.SH DESCRIPTION
procvw is a process inspection tool designed for FreeBSD. It supports
both flat and hierarchical (tree) views of processes, as well as JSON
export and snapshot loading. Its output can be colored if so wanted.

The tool can operate on live system data or previously saved JSON snapshots.

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B \-u, \-\-user USER
Filter the processes by user.

.TP
.B \-f, \-\-filter STRING
Filter the processes by a command substring.

.TP
.B \-p, \-\-pid PID
Filter by specific process ID.

.TP
.B \-s, \-\-sort {cpu,mem,pid,rss,thr,cmd}
Sort the processes by CPU, memory, PID, RSS, thread, or command.

.TP
.B \-b, \-\-bottom
Reverse sort order (ascending).

.TP
.B \-n, \-\-number NUMBER
Limit number of displayed processes or nodes.

.TP
.B \-\-color
Enable colored output.

.TP
.B \-\-tree
Display process hierarchy as a tree.

.TP
.B \-\-table
When loading JSON files with the --load flag, processes can be displayed in
table format by using this flag.´

.TP
.B \-\-cpu-all
Show subtree CPU usage for all nodes.

.TP
.B \-\-cpu-threshold VALUE
Only display CPU usage above threshold.

.TP
.B \-\-depth N
Limit depth of tree view.

.TP
.B \-\-json
Output full process data as JSON.

.TP
.B \-\-json-view
Output JSON matching visible tree.

.TP
.B \-\-save FILE
Save output to JSON file.

.TP
.B \-\-load FILE
Load process data from JSON file instead of live system.

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
Show top processes by CPU:
.B procvw \-s cpu

.TP
Tree view with color:
.B procvw \-\-tree \-\-color

.TP
Save snapshot:
.B procvw \-\-save snapshot.json

.TP
Load snapshot:
.B procvw \-\-load snapshot.json

.TP
Load and show as table:
.B procvw \-\-load snapshot.json \-\-table

